css`**\n\n```css\n@tailwind base;\n@tailwind components;\n@tailwind utilities;\n\n@layer base {\n  body {\n    background-color: #fffdf7;\n    color: #1a1a1a;\n  }\n}\n\n/* react-masonry-css */\n.masonry-grid {\n  display: flex;\n  gap: 10px;\n}\n.masonry-grid-column {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  gap: 10px;\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Replace `app/layout.tsx` with fonts + shell layout**\n\n```tsx\nimport type { Metadata } from 'next'\nimport { Playfair_Display, Inter } from 'next/font/google'\nimport './globals.css'\n\nconst playfair = Playfair_Display({\n  subsets: ['latin'],\n  variable: '--font-playfair',\n  display: 'swap',\n})\n\nconst inter = Inter({\n  subsets: ['latin'],\n  variable: '--font-inter',\n  display: 'swap',\n})\n\nexport const metadata: Metadata = {\n  title: 'Vincent Ng',\n  description: 'Full-stack developer specialising in AI-powered systems and scalable cloud infrastructure.',\n}\n\nexport default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {\n  return (\n    <html lang=\"en\" className={`${playfair.variable} ${inter.variable}`}>\n      <body className=\"bg-cream font-sans antialiased\">\n        {children}\n      </body>\n    </html>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Create placeholder public directories**\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p public/photos public/projects\ntouch public/photos/.gitkeep public/projects/.gitkeep\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit the scaffold**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"chore: scaffold Next.js 14 project with Tailwind and design tokens\"\n```\n\n## Context\n\nThis is a brand new personal portfolio website for Vincent Ng — a full-stack developer and photographer. The project directory is `e:/GitProject/awesome-big-V`. The repo already exists with only docs (no source code yet). You are scaffolding the Next.js app into this existing directory.\n\nKey design decisions already locked in:\n- Warm Editorial theme: cream background (#fffdf7), serif headings (Playfair Display), body text in Inter\n- Custom Tailwind colour tokens: cream, ink, ink-body, ink-muted, parchment\n- Three pages: Home (/), Career (/career), Gallery (/gallery)\n- App Router (not Pages Router)\n\nThe `--no-git` flag is important — the git repo already exists, don't reinitialise it.\n\nAfter `create-next-app` runs, it will generate default files. You need to REPLACE `tailwind.config.ts`, `app/globals.css`, and `app/layout.tsx` with the project-specific versions in the steps above. Also delete the default `app/page.tsx` content (it will be replaced in Task 4) but leave the file so the build doesn't fail — replace its content with a simple placeholder:\n\n```tsx\nexport default function HomePage() {\n  return <main className=\"max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20\"><p className=\"font-sans text-ink-muted\">Coming soon.</p></main>\n}\n```\n\n## Before You Begin\n\nIf you have questions about the requirements or approach, ask now before starting.\n\n## Your Job\n\n1. Implement exactly what the task specifies\n2. Verify `npm run build` passes with zero TypeScript errors after scaffold\n3. Commit your work\n4. Self-review and report back\n\nWork from: `e:/GitProject/awesome-big-V`\n\n## Report Format\n\nWhen done, report:\n- **Status:** DONE | DONE_WITH_CONCERNS | BLOCKED | NEEDS_CONTEXT\n- What you implemented\n- Files changed\n- Self-review findings\n- Any concerns\n","mode":"auto"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_014R7Kv2npyAH2RLGJNYySgN"}
